column1: Karametra went "OFF" with a huge squad of hasty, lifelinking, vigilence, flying, pro-red/black creatures.  knocking out Niv and SakaSmasher in one turn punishing them for 1) resolving a Niv and 2) attempting to notion thief wheel the table (notably squashed by Scarab God's interaction);  Then Scarab God gave Karametra a dose of her own medecine by "Tergrid'ing" both Vorinclex's and a bunch of other creatures, lands and a Mirari's Wake.  Then finally "hostage taker'ing" her Akroma'sMemorial and smashing back for lethal.
Player 3: Brendan / Vial Smasher + Sakashima of a Thousand Faces

column1:
Early bulky lad's Mirari's wake got krosan gripped (sad tibalt trickery in hand was *not* very effective);  Then two big dragon decks set up draw engines; mana engines and lotsaaa dragons.  EOT 5cScion binned a helluva bunch of dragons and tried to resolve a Patriarch's bidding on his next turn.....
key word "tried" as Ur-Doddy top-decked a counterspell in the clutchiest of clutch moments saving the table from the mass reanimation spell.  Bulky lads slowly rebuilt after a Cylconic Rift and was able to re-direct the aggression for a turn-cycle with a Gisela and block out some big dragons.  Ur-Doddy swung in for to kill 5cScion and made ~42 mana (!!!) between Klauth and Old Gnawbones and dumped his hand.  ending his turn with a huge board, buuut only 6 life.  Bulky lads unwittingly wins the game with 7 tiny creatures pumped up by Big Kamahl. What a game!

column1: Penultimate Turn Cycle: Teysa nearly combo'd off, but wasn't able to stick a Cruel Celebrant due to 2 counterspells (1 for CC; 1 for animate dead), so he had to settle for 990,000 white spirit tokens.  Ended his turn with an Elesh Norn and T-Pro (Bye!).   Bren (Wort) has a magnificent Gruul storm turn, digging for an instant speed way to kill Alex on his upkeep when he phases back in from T-Pro.  Wort spends 20m chaining Escape to the wilds &Mana Geyser off conspire and U-Breach. Sticks a Purphy and starts to make tokens.  John T-Pro's out (Bye!).  Bub's dies to the Purpy.  So its literally just Wort and 2 phased out players (alex and john).  Wort continues digging; Finds an answer. Waits for upkeep. Alex untaps.  Wort Electrodominance's Alex's face for 8 and makes 3 tokens for free.  Alex exiles Purphy in reponse so the tokens don't deal the final 6 lethal dmg.  Alex goes to combat and swings 100 of his 998,997 white spirit tokens at Bren.  John untaps and phases back in from T-Pro. Alex holds priority to Swords the Linvala, Keeper of Silence who is shushing Alex's sac outlets (teysa & carrion feeder).  In response John casts Rakdos charm, doming Alex for 998,998 damage.  GG.
